	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />- Ah, yes, one case: the MMC3 (mapper 4).
<br />
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">=== PRG RAM protect &#40;$A001-$BFFF, odd&#41; ===<br />&nbsp;7&nbsp; bit&nbsp; 0<br />&nbsp;---- ----<br />&nbsp;RWxx xxxx<br />&nbsp;||<br />&nbsp;|+-------- Write protection &#40;0: allow writes; 1: deny writes&#41;<br />&nbsp;+--------- Chip enable &#40;0: disable chip; 1: enable chip&#41;</div>
<br />
<br />- So, if the chip is disabled, what would a WRAM read return?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
